    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Approved. 33 vocab + 30 grammar, one structure — Present perfect (+ just) — across 13 formats, the health/injury world. Grant: ~36 common past participles (broken/eaten/seen/made/done/gone/written/taken/lost/won/found/given…) + the body parts head/back/arm (taught only inside headache/backache). Past-SIMPLE forms (broke/ate) are NOT granted, so the agent's wrong-participle distractors use regularized errors (maked/writed/hurted — which lemmatize through the gate as authentic kid mistakes) + wrong-aux/word-order. Zero glosses. Smoke-check fixed 3 empty sentence-building pools, 4 group-sort/pair items with non-empty answers (those grade from groups/pairs), the \"past participle\" jargon in 5 hints (→ German \"3. Form\"), and 2 spelling-variant answers (lamppost/stomachache → partial). Verify round 1: replaced a true-synonym distractor (cure/medicine) and added an uncontracted free-form partial; round 2 clean. Present-perfect participle correctness + just-placement keyed correctly throughout. 36 translations adjudicated; 2 \"Sie\" warns are the subject pronoun (\"die Form\"), not formal address. rejectRate 0.0%."
